Gender View instructions 12

1.   Go to the DataSource Tab

2.  On the Top Right, next to Extract, click on Edit, click on Add and Select Gender.


3. Right Click and Duplicate the No IT Exp worksheet

4. Rename it to Gender

5. Remove all pills from the columns and shelves.


6. Drag _cc.Duplicate 1 onto Rows. Then Right Click it and Select Dimension.


7. In the Marks Card, replace _cc.IT.Exp% with _cc.FemaleGender% , in Detail



8. In the Marks Card, Replace _cc.GenderMale>Female with Gender, for Color.



9. In the Marks Card, Change the Shape to Pie



10. In the Marks card, drag Marketing Demographics (Count) into Angle.

 

11. In the Marks Card, click on Color, Edit Color and select Blue for Male and Pink for Female



12. Right Click the Y Axis and uncheck Show Header.



13. Click on Entire View

14. In the Marks Card, click on Size. Adjust the slider to around 80%(take a guess).



15. Right Click in the Worksheet and select Format.

16. Click on the Lines icon, click on Zero Lines and select None.


17. Double Click on Title.

18. Highlight Missing Field. Click on Insert and select _cc.FemaleGender% and replace No IT exp with Female
